SIMPLE: preference
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preference
<hw>Pref"er*ence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧f⟦eacute⟧rence</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
Preferring, or the state of being preferred; the setting of one thing
before another; precedence; higher estimation; predilection; choice;
also, the power or opportunity of choosing; <as>as, to give him his
<ex>preference</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Leave the critics on either side to contend about the
<qex>preference</qex> due to this or that sort of poetry.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Knowledge of things alone gives a value to our reasonings, and
<qex>preference</qex> of one man's knowledge over another's.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is preferred; the object of choice or
superior favor; as, which is your <xex>preference</xex>?</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preferential</ent>⟦br⟧
